{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SUSXLm65aXZxgAWUuuBwEs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8-7: Rust OTLP Instrumentation\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer instrumenting a Rust project,\n     8→I want codeharness to add OpenTelemetry crates and provide setup guidance,\n     9→So that I can quickly enable observability.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a Rust project, when `instrumentProject()` runs, then `cargo add opentelemetry opentelemetry-otlp tracing-opentelemetry tracing-subscriber` is executed <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given OTLP instrumentation succeeds, when state is updated, then `configureOtlpEnvVars()` writes `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` and `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` to `.env.codeharness` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a Rust project, when `configureAgent()` is called, then it skips with info message (no standard Rust agent SDK yet) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Given `templates/otlp/rust.md` exists, when read, then it contains: packages to add, `tracing_subscriber` setup code snippet, `#[tracing::instrument]` usage, env vars, verification steps <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Technical Notes\n    19→\n    20→### OTLP Crate Installation\n    21→\n    22→File: `src/lib/otlp.ts` — ~330 lines.\n    23→\n    24→Add constant at module level:\n    25→```typescript\n    26→const RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES = ['opentelemetry', 'opentelemetry-otlp', 'tracing-opentelemetry', 'tracing-subscriber'];\n    27→```\n    28→\n    29→Create `installRustOtlp(baseDir: string)` function:\n    30→1. Run `cargo add opentelemetry opentelemetry-otlp tracing-opentelemetry tracing-subscriber` from project root\n    31→2. Follow the pattern of existing `installNodeOtlp()` and `installPythonOtlp()` functions\n    32→3. If `cargo add` fails (not in a cargo project), return failed status\n    33→\n    34→### instrumentProject() Integration\n    35→\n    36→File: `src/lib/otlp.ts` — `instrumentProject()` at L295 (approx L309 per tech spec).\n    37→\n    38→Add `else if (stack === 'rust')` branch that calls `installRustOtlp()`.\n    39→\n    40→### Environment Variable Configuration\n    41→\n    42→File: `src/lib/otlp.ts` — `configureOtlpEnvVars()` at L258-274.\n    43→\n    44→Add Rust case: write `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` and `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` to `.env.codeharness`. Store `{ rust_env_hint: 'OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT' }` in state (requires story 8-2 state type expansion).\n    45→\n    46→### Agent Configuration\n    47→\n    48→File: `src/lib/otlp.ts` — `configureAgent()` at L207-227.\n    49→\n    50→Add Rust case: no standard agent SDK for Rust yet. Skip with info message (e.g., `log.info('Rust agent SDK not yet supported — skipping agent configuration')`).\n    51→\n    52→### LLM Guidance Document\n    53→\n    54→File: `templates/otlp/rust.md` (new).\n    55→\n    56→Follow the pattern of `templates/otlp/nodejs.md` (54 lines) and `templates/otlp/python.md` (52 lines). Include:\n    57→1. **Packages to add**: `cargo add opentelemetry opentelemetry-otlp tracing-opentelemetry tracing-subscriber`\n    58→2. **Setup code snippet**: `tracing_subscriber` initialization with OTLP exporter layer in `main.rs`\n    59→3. **Function instrumentation**: `#[tracing::instrument]` attribute usage\n    60→4. **Environment variables**: `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT`, `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME`\n    61→5. **Verification steps**: How to confirm traces are being exported\n    62→\n    63→This is guidance for the LLM, not auto-generated code. Keep concise and practical.\n    64→\n    65→### Tests\n    66→\n    67→File: `src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts`\n    68→\n    69→Mirror existing Node.js/Python test patterns with `vi.mock('node:child_process')`. Test cases:\n    70→- `installRustOtlp()` success → runs `cargo add` with correct packages\n    71→- `installRustOtlp()` failure → returns failed status\n    72→- `instrumentProject()` with stack `'rust'` → calls `installRustOtlp()`\n    73→- `configureOtlpEnvVars()` with stack `'rust'` → writes env vars\n    74→- `configureAgent()` with stack `'rust'` → skips with info message\n    75→\n    76→## Files to Change\n    77→\n    78→- `src/lib/otlp.ts` — Add `RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES` constant, add `installRustOtlp()` function, add Rust branch to `instrumentProject()` (L309), add Rust case to `configureOtlpEnvVars()` (L268), add Rust case to `configureAgent()` (L207)\n    79→- `templates/otlp/rust.md` (new) — Create LLM guidance doc for Rust OTLP instrumentation with setup code, attribute usage, env vars, and verification steps\n    80→- `src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` — Add Rust OTLP test cases for installation, instrumentation, env vars, and agent config skip\n    81→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0171dfRPdau3d9vdSdBsjERK","session_id":"8e4c6a49-a8f5-4820-a234-101957ee0803","uuid":"64a620f8-0243-4033-bbc7-4860b563fd34","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:33:50.034Z"}
