{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016eNSRqFDWiMdo5vV9m1Jha","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e4c6a49-a8f5-4820-a234-101957ee0803","uuid":"f649aa8f-d694-4d27-8aab-dbfc3c88f346","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:36:28.868Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile — verify attempt 1 (2026-03-23T11:28Z)\n\n- **CRITICAL BUG FOUND:** package.json `files` array missing `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`. Template files existed in source but not shipped in npm package. Fixed by adding entries to `files` array.\n- **Cache invalidation issue:** After fixing package.json, `codeharness verify-env build` reported \"up to date (cached)\" because it hashes only `dist/` contents. Had to manually invalidate the stored dist hash in `.claude/codeharness.local.md`.\n- **Escalated ACs (valid):** AC7 (Docker-in-Docker) and AC8 (npm test in black-box) are genuinely impossible in black-box mode.\n- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed — recurring across all sessions.","newString":"### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile — verify attempt 1 (2026-03-23T11:28Z)\n\n- **CRITICAL BUG FOUND:** package.json `files` array missing `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`. Template files existed in source but not shipped in npm package. Fixed by adding entries to `files` array.\n- **Cache invalidation issue:** After fixing package.json, `codeharness verify-env build` reported \"up to date (cached)\" because it hashes only `dist/` contents. Had to manually invalidate the stored dist hash in `.claude/codeharness.local.md`.\n- **Escalated ACs (valid):** AC7 (Docker-in-Docker) and AC8 (npm test in black-box) are genuinely impossible in black-box mode.\n- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed — recurring across all sessions.\n\n### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — create-story (2026-03-23T11:35Z)\n\n- **Bug found in existing code:** `configureAgent()` falls through to set `agent_sdk: 'traceloop'` for Rust projects — no Rust Traceloop SDK exists. Story task 4 fixes this.\n- **Scope expansion:** AC2 requires writing `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness` — current code only writes `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` there. Necessary for Rust apps that read env vars directly.\n- **Risk: otlp.ts at 375 lines**, will grow to ~410 (exceeds 300-line NFR1 limit). Pre-existing violation.\n- **Risk: AC8 integration-required** — needs real Rust toolchain + `cargo` for full pipeline verification.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 3)\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n\n- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n\n- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — verify (2026-03-23T10:17Z)\n\n- **CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.\n- **AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.\n- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected — container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.\n- **Workspace aggregation confirmed.** Bundle shows `parseTestCounts` uses global regex with `matchAll`-style loop for multi-crate workspace test output.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — create-story (2026-03-23T09:22Z)\n\n- **Unconditional dependency registry:** Adding `cargo-tarpaulin` means `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on all projects regardless of stack. Fails gracefully (`critical: false`) but is noisy. Stack-conditional filtering would be a separate story.\n- **Pre-existing stub overwritten:** The file already existed as a skeleton from sprint planning. Overwritten with comprehensive story as expected.\n- **Risk: deps-install.test.ts mock registry:** Consumer test mocks `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` with hardcoded single-entry array. Mock isolates consumer from registry changes — no update needed there.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — dev-story (2026-03-23T09:28Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing test failures:** 4 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts` when run as full suite — test isolation issue, not related to this story.\n- **Unconditional registry design acknowledged:** `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on non-Rust projects. `critical: false` handles graceful failure. Stack-conditional filtering deferred.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — code-review (2026-03-23T09:35Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale — deps.ts description omitted cargo-tarpaulin from tool list.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Story File List empty — no files documented in Dev Agent Record.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Fragile catch-all mock in installAllDependencies tests — implicitly handles cargo-tarpaulin via fallthrough rather than explicit mock branch.\n- Coverage: 97% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — verify (2026-03-23T09:42Z)\n\n- All 5 ACs passed black-box verification.\n- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed — recurring issue across sessions.\n- **Showboat not installed warning** during `codeharness verify` — non-blocking but means no re-verification via showboat.\n- No observability gaps reported by verifier for this story.\n\n### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template — create-story (2026-03-23T10:41Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing stub overwritten:** Stub story file already existed from earlier epic planning. Overwritten with comprehensive version.\n- **Workflow naming mismatch:** workflow.md referenced in skill was actually workflow.yaml — minor.\n- **Risk: checkNoSourceCopy validator false positive:** The `COPY src/` pattern in the validator regex could false-match on Rust template's `COPY . .` builder stage. Story documents this prominently but dev agent could miss it.\n- **Risk: AC7 integration-required:** Depends on `detectStack()` returning `'rust'` for real Rust project during `codeharness init`. Cannot verify purely via unit tests.\n\n### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template — dev-story (2026-03-23T10:45Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing test failure:** `modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` line 261 fails (`migrateFromOldFormat` returns `success: false`). Unrelated to this story.\n- **No workarounds applied.** Implementation follows existing patterns exactly.\n- **34/34 dockerfile-template tests pass.** 2994/2995 full suite (1 pre-existing failure).\n\n### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template — verify (2026-03-23T10:57Z)\n\n- **Proof format issue:** AC3 and AC4 referenced AC2's Dockerfile output without their own `bash`+`output` code blocks. Proof validator counted them as \"pending\" (5/7). Fixed by adding per-AC grep evidence blocks.\n- **Observability gap:** All 7 ACs showed no log events in VictoriaLogs. Recurring pattern — CLI commands don't emit telemetry in verify container.\n- **Beads sync skipped:** `bd` binary not installed (recurring).\n- **Showboat re-verification skipped:** showboat not installed (recurring).\n\n### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template — code-review (2026-03-23T10:50Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Missing showboat proof document — created with AC-by-AC evidence.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale — omitted rust from dockerfile-template.ts entry.\n- **MEDIUM (not fixed, design decision):** Rust template has no ENTRYPOINT/CMD — consistent with all other templates.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Hardcoded `rust:1.82-slim` will age. Users edit the template.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Error-path tests only exercise nodejs stack (code is stack-agnostic).\n- Coverage: 97% overall, 100% for dockerfile-template.ts, all files above 80% floor.\n\n### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile — create-story (2026-03-23T11:10Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity: showboat installation in Rust image.** Epic says \"showboat\" but doesn't mention it's an npm package requiring Node.js. Prior draft incorrectly listed `pipx install showboat`. Story now documents Node.js dependency.\n- **Risk: env.ts approaching 300-line limit.** File is 293 lines. Adding `buildRustImage()` puts it around ~308 lines.\n- **Observation: prior draft existed.** Minimal draft (74 lines, 2 ACs) overwritten with comprehensive version (217 lines, 8 ACs, 8 tasks).\n\n### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile — dev-story (2026-03-23T11:17Z)\n\n- **Task 5.2 deviation:** Story specified copying Cargo.toml/Cargo.lock/src into build context. Dev Notes clarified this is a tools-only image (project mounted at runtime), so buildRustImage follows buildGenericImage pattern with Dockerfile-only context. Task marked complete despite deviation.\n- **Build timeout:** buildRustImage uses 300s timeout (vs 120s for others) because cargo install cargo-tarpaulin compiles from source. Minor pattern deviation.\n- **env.ts line count:** File grew from 293 to ~307 lines, slightly over 300-line soft limit.\n\n### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile — code-review (2026-03-23T11:24Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** NFR9 violation — env.ts was 307 lines (> 300 limit). Merged buildRustImage and buildGenericImage into buildSimpleImage helper. Now 299 lines.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unreadable nested ternary in resolveDockerfileTemplate. Replaced with DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS lookup map.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Stale comment in hash-skip section.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale — didn't document Rust as supported project type.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Tests cast 'rust' as ReturnType<typeof detectStack> unnecessarily.\n- **Coverage gap:** No test for buildSimpleImage timeout parameter propagation (Rust 300s vs generic 120s).\n- **Coverage gap:** AC7 integration test marked integration-required — needs Docker verification.\n\n### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile — verify attempt 1 (2026-03-23T11:28Z)\n\n- **CRITICAL BUG FOUND:** package.json `files` array missing `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`. Template files existed in source but not shipped in npm package. Fixed by adding entries to `files` array.\n- **Cache invalidation issue:** After fixing package.json, `codeharness verify-env build` reported \"up to date (cached)\" because it hashes only `dist/` contents. Had to manually invalidate the stored dist hash in `.claude/codeharness.local.md`.\n- **Escalated ACs (valid):** AC7 (Docker-in-Docker) and AC8 (npm test in black-box) are genuinely impossible in black-box mode.\n- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed — recurring across all sessions.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":116,"oldLines":3,"newStart":116,"newLines":10,"lines":[" - **Cache invalidation issue:** After fixing package.json, `codeharness verify-env build` reported \"up to date (cached)\" because it hashes only `dist/` contents. Had to manually invalidate the stored dist hash in `.claude/codeharness.local.md`."," - **Escalated ACs (valid):** AC7 (Docker-in-Docker) and AC8 (npm test in black-box) are genuinely impossible in black-box mode."," - **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed — recurring across all sessions.","+","+### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — create-story (2026-03-23T11:35Z)","+","+- **Bug found in existing code:** `configureAgent()` falls through to set `agent_sdk: 'traceloop'` for Rust projects — no Rust Traceloop SDK exists. Story task 4 fixes this.","+- **Scope expansion:** AC2 requires writing `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness` — current code only writes `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` there. Necessary for Rust apps that read env vars directly.","+- **Risk: otlp.ts at 375 lines**, will grow to ~410 (exceeds 300-line NFR1 limit). Pre-existing violation.","+- **Risk: AC8 integration-required** — needs real Rust toolchain + `cargo` for full pipeline verification."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
