{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015sdAUqgT2h4yvHQdc3eHYB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is what was done:\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/otlp.ts` — Added `RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES` constant, `installRustOtlp()` function, `ensureEndpointEnvVar()` helper, updated `instrumentProject()` Rust branch to call `installRustOtlp()`, added Rust branch to `configureAgent()` that skips with info message, added `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` writing to `.env.codeharness` for Rust in `configureOtlpEnvVars()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` — Added 13 new test cases covering `installRustOtlp` (success, failure, truncation, package list), `configureOtlpEnvVars` Rust endpoint writing, `configureAgent` Rust skip behavior, and `instrumentProject` Rust end-to-end flow\n\n**File created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/templates/otlp/rust.md` — LLM guidance doc with `cargo add` command, `tracing_subscriber` setup code, `#[tracing::instrument]` usage, env vars, and verification steps\n\n**Story file updated:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation.md` — Status set to `review`, all task checkboxes marked complete\n\n**Test results:** 75/75 OTLP tests pass. 307/307 BATS tests pass. 6 pre-existing failures in sprint migration/state tests (unrelated to this story).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing test failures:** 6 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` and `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts`. These are unrelated to story 8-7 changes — they test sprint state management, not OTLP. Story 8-6 notes \"2998 tests pass\" but the current suite shows 3010 total with 6 failures, suggesting these broke between 8-6 and now.\n- **Mock isolation quirk:** The `installRustOtlp` test \"includes all four Rust OTLP packages\" initially failed because `vi.restoreAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` doesn't fully clear `mock.calls` on module-level `vi.mock`'d functions. Added explicit `mockClear()` to fix. The same pattern exists in the Node.js equivalent test but doesn't fail there due to test ordering. This is a minor fragility in the test setup.\n- **File line count:** `otlp.ts` is now ~423 lines, exceeding the 300-line NFR1 limit noted in dev notes. The story itself acknowledges this overage. The `ensureEndpointEnvVar` function duplicates the pattern from `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` — these could be consolidated into a generic `ensureEnvVar(projectDir, key, value)` helper to reduce duplication."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a32af0370df6080bb (use SendMessage with to: 'a32af0370df6080bb' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61283\ntool_uses: 49\nduration_ms: 804761</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e4c6a49-a8f5-4820-a234-101957ee0803","uuid":"8bc659f8-71c3-4bd7-875f-f9fde816ee74","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:50:11.794Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a32af0370df6080bb","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is what was done:\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/otlp.ts` — Added `RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES` constant, `installRustOtlp()` function, `ensureEndpointEnvVar()` helper, updated `instrumentProject()` Rust branch to call `installRustOtlp()`, added Rust branch to `configureAgent()` that skips with info message, added `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` writing to `.env.codeharness` for Rust in `configureOtlpEnvVars()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` — Added 13 new test cases covering `installRustOtlp` (success, failure, truncation, package list), `configureOtlpEnvVars` Rust endpoint writing, `configureAgent` Rust skip behavior, and `instrumentProject` Rust end-to-end flow\n\n**File created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/templates/otlp/rust.md` — LLM guidance doc with `cargo add` command, `tracing_subscriber` setup code, `#[tracing::instrument]` usage, env vars, and verification steps\n\n**Story file updated:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation.md` — Status set to `review`, all task checkboxes marked complete\n\n**Test results:** 75/75 OTLP tests pass. 307/307 BATS tests pass. 6 pre-existing failures in sprint migration/state tests (unrelated to this story).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing test failures:** 6 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` and `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts`. These are unrelated to story 8-7 changes — they test sprint state management, not OTLP. Story 8-6 notes \"2998 tests pass\" but the current suite shows 3010 total with 6 failures, suggesting these broke between 8-6 and now.\n- **Mock isolation quirk:** The `installRustOtlp` test \"includes all four Rust OTLP packages\" initially failed because `vi.restoreAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` doesn't fully clear `mock.calls` on module-level `vi.mock`'d functions. Added explicit `mockClear()` to fix. The same pattern 