{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SZmt5p7fxp3mdcs7gAsRJn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 3)\n     2→\n     3→### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — create-story (2026-03-23T11:35Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Bug found in existing code:** `configureAgent()` falls through to set `agent_sdk: 'traceloop'` for Rust projects — no Rust Traceloop SDK exists. Story task 4 fixes this.\n     6→- **Scope expansion:** AC2 requires writing `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness` — current code only writes `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` there. Necessary for Rust apps that read env vars directly.\n     7→- **Risk: otlp.ts at 375 lines**, will grow to ~410 (exceeds 300-line NFR1 limit). Pre-existing violation.\n     8→- **Risk: AC8 integration-required** — needs real Rust toolchain + `cargo` for full pipeline verification.\n     9→\n    10→### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — dev-story (2026-03-23T11:50Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **Pre-existing test failures:** 6 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` and `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts`. Unrelated to story 8-7. May have broken between 8-6 and now.\n    13→- **Mock isolation quirk:** `installRustOtlp` test needed explicit `mockClear()` because `vi.restoreAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` doesn't fully clear `mock.calls` on module-level `vi.mock`'d functions. Minor fragility.\n    14→- **File line count:** `otlp.ts` is now ~423 lines, exceeding the 300-line NFR1 limit. `ensureEndpointEnvVar` duplicates pattern from `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` — could be consolidated.\n    15→- **Sprint-status.yaml corruption:** The dev-story agent overwrote sprint-status.yaml with placeholder content. Had to restore from git and manually set status to `review`.\n    16→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JtCKTdcL6qUa2gmE9ZsXx6","session_id":"8e4c6a49-a8f5-4820-a234-101957ee0803","uuid":"be69963e-044f-4ea2-a7bc-f23a61188388","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:51:50.788Z"}
