{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012qH7btjYZBj1FqVRsB3o4A","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8-7: Rust OTLP Instrumentation\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer instrumenting a Rust project,\n    10→I want codeharness to add OpenTelemetry crates and provide setup guidance,\n    11→so that I can quickly enable observability.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **AC1:** Given a Rust project, when `instrumentProject()` runs, then `cargo add opentelemetry opentelemetry-otlp tracing-opentelemetry tracing-subscriber` is executed and `packages_installed` returns `true` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **AC2:** Given OTLP instrumentation succeeds on a Rust project, when state is updated, then `configureOtlpEnvVars()` writes `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` and `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` to `.env.codeharness` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **AC3:** Given a Rust project, when `configureAgent()` is called, then it skips with info message (no standard Rust agent SDK yet) and does NOT install any packages or set `agent_sdk` in state <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. **AC4:** Given `templates/otlp/rust.md` exists, when read, then it contains: packages to add (`cargo add` command), `tracing_subscriber` setup code snippet, `#[tracing::instrument]` usage, environment variables (`OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT`, `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME`), and verification steps <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. **AC5:** Given `installRustOtlp()` is called and `cargo add` fails, then it returns `{ status: 'failed', packages_installed: false }` with an error message <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. **AC6:** Given a Rust project, when `instrumentProject()` runs in non-json mode, then it prints an info message about Rust OTLP packages being installed <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. **AC7:** Given all changes, when `npm test` runs, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions and new Rust OTLP tests pass <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→8. **AC8:** Given `codeharness init` runs on a Rust project, when the OTLP instrumentation phase executes, then it runs `cargo add` for the OTLP crates (not just env vars) <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    23→\n    24→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    25→\n    26→- [x] Task 1: Add `RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES` constant and `installRustOtlp()` function to `src/lib/otlp.ts` (AC: #1, #5)\n    27→  - [x]1.1 Add `const RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES = ['opentelemetry', 'opentelemetry-otlp', 'tracing-opentelemetry', 'tracing-subscriber'];` after `PYTHON_OTLP_PACKAGES`\n    28→  - [x]1.2 Create `installRustOtlp(projectDir: string): OtlpResult` following `installNodeOtlp()` pattern\n    29→  - [x]1.3 Run `cargo add opentelemetry opentelemetry-otlp tracing-opentelemetry tracing-subscriber` via `execFileSync`\n    30→  - [x]1.4 Return `{ status: 'configured', packages_installed: true, ... }` on success\n    31→  - [x]1.5 Return `{ status: 'failed', packages_installed: false, error: '...' }` on failure with truncated error message\n    32→- [x] Task 2: Update `instrumentProject()` Rust branch to call `installRustOtlp()` (AC: #1, #6)\n    33→  - [x]2.1 Replace the current placeholder Rust branch (L318-329) with actual `installRustOtlp()` call\n    34→  - [x]2.2 On success, print `ok('OTLP: Rust packages installed')` in non-json mode\n    35→  - [x]2.3 On failure, the existing error handling path covers it (L369-371)\n    36→- [x] Task 3: Add `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness` for Rust (AC: #2)\n    37→  - [x]3.1 In `configureOtlpEnvVars()`, after calling `ensureServiceNameEnvVar()`, add Rust-specific logic to also write `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness` (Rust reads env vars directly, unlike Node.js `--require` or Python wrapper)\n    38→  - [x]3.2 Use same file append/update pattern as `ensureServiceNameEnvVar()`\n    39→- [x] Task 4: Add Rust case to `configureAgent()` — skip with info (AC: #3)\n    40→  - [x]4.1 Add `else if (stack === 'rust')` branch after the Python branch (L227)\n    41→  - [x]4.2 Log info message: `info('Rust agent SDK not yet supported — skipping agent configuration')`\n    42→  - [x]4.3 Return early — do NOT set `agent_sdk` in state (no Rust agent SDK exists)\n    43→- [x] Task 5: Create `templates/otlp/rust.md` (AC: #4)\n    44→  - [x]5.1 Follow pattern of `templates/otlp/nodejs.md` (54 lines) and `templates/otlp/python.md` (52 lines)\n    45→  - [x]5.2 Section: Packages to Install — `cargo add opentelemetry opentelemetry-otlp tracing-opentelemetry tracing-subscriber`\n    46→  - [x]5.3 Section: Setup Code — `tracing_subscriber` initialization with OTLP exporter layer in `main.rs`\n    47→  - [x]5.4 Section: Function Instrumentation — `#[tracing::instrument]` attribute usage\n    48→  - [x]5.5 Section: Environment Variables — `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT`, `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME`, etc.\n    49→  - [x]5.6 Section: Verification — How to confirm traces are being exported\n    50→- [x] Task 6: Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #5, #6, #7)\n    51→  - [x]6.1 Test: `installRustOtlp()` success — runs `cargo add` with correct packages\n    52→  - [x]6.2 Test: `installRustOtlp()` failure — returns failed status with error message\n    53→  - [x]6.3 Test: `instrumentProject()` with stack `'rust'` — calls `cargo add` and returns `packages_installed: true`\n    54→  - [x]6.4 Test: `instrumentProject()` Rust prints info message in non-json mode\n    55→  - [x]6.5 Test: `configureOtlpEnvVars()` with stack `'rust'` — writes `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness`\n    56→  - [x]6.6 Test: `configureAgent()` with stack `'rust'` — skips without installing packages or setting agent_sdk\n    57→  - [x]6.7 Test: `installRustOtlp()` truncates long error messages\n    58→- [x] Task 7: Run full test suite — zero regressions (AC: #7)\n    59→\n    60→## Dev Notes"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JtCKTdcL6qUa2gmE9ZsXx6","session_id":"8e4c6a49-a8f5-4820-a234-101957ee0803","uuid":"7764ba7a-745f-43dd-be59-edd2a28f1294","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:52:28.322Z"}
