{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017eEmUCWoYxCYNNnUmskbdE","type":"tool_result","content":"   850→- **Black-box verification catches packaging bugs that unit tests never will.** The `package.json` files array bug is invisible to `npm test` but fatal to users. Always verify in a container.\n   851→- **Code review before verification.** The `env.ts` refactoring (307 -> 299 lines) happened during review, before the verifier saw the code. Clean code is easier to verify.\n   852→\n   853→### Avoid\n   854→\n   855→- **Do not assume `files` array in `package.json` is complete.** Every new template file needs a corresponding entry. Consider adding a CI check that verifies all `templates/` files are listed in `package.json` `files`.\n   856→- **Do not rely on `dist/` hash for build cache invalidation.** Template changes are invisible to the current cache. Fix the hash to include `templates/` directory.\n   857→\n   858→---\n   859→\n   860→## 6. Action Items\n   861→\n   862→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   863→\n   864→- [ ] Reconcile `.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-status.yaml` -- 8-5 and 8-6 should be `done`, sprint done count should be 31\n   865→- [ ] Verify `package.json` `files` array includes all `templates/` files (prevent recurrence of CRITICAL bug)\n   866→\n   867→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   868→\n   869→- [ ] **Extend build cache hash to include `templates/` directory** -- template-only changes currently bypass cache invalidation\n   870→- [ ] **Add CI check that all `templates/*` files are listed in `package.json` `files` array** -- prevents shipping incomplete npm packages\n   871→- [ ] **Track escalated ACs** -- 8-5 and 8-6 each have ACs that need Docker-in-Docker integration testing\n   872→- [ ] **Add timeout propagation test** for `buildSimpleImage` (Rust 300s vs generic 120s)\n   873→\n   874→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   875→\n   876→- [ ] Remove unnecessary `ReturnType<typeof detectStack>` casts in env tests\n   877→- [ ] Add Docker-in-Docker integration test environment for escalated ACs\n   878→\n   879→---\n   880→\n   881→## Session Metrics (Final -- Addendum 5)\n   882→\n   883→| Metric | Value |\n   884→|--------|-------|\n   885→| Stories completed this addendum | 1 (8-6) |\n   886→| Stories completed total (session) | 6 (8-1 through 8-6) |\n   887→| Stories failed | 0 |\n   888→| Bugs found (this addendum) | 5 (1 CRITICAL, 3 MEDIUM, 1 LOW) |\n   889→| Bugs found total (session) | 19 (1 CRITICAL, 5 HIGH, 12 MEDIUM, 1 LOW) |\n   890→| Bugs shipped unfixed | 0 HIGH/MEDIUM/CRITICAL, 8 LOW (accepted) |\n   891→| Ralph iterations total | 7 |\n   892→| Timeouts | 1 (iteration 1) |\n   893→| Commits total | 7 |\n   894→| Sprint progress | 25/34 -> 31/34 (91%) |\n   895→| Epics completed this session | 3 full (Epic 8.1, 8.2, 8.3) |\n   896→| Remaining backlog | 3 stories (8-7, 8-8, 8-9 in Epic 8.4-8.5) |\n   897→| Recurring issues unfixed | 9 (+1 build cache hash) |\n   898→| Session velocity | ~6 stories / ~135 min = 1 story per ~22.5 min avg |\n   899→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JtCKTdcL6qUa2gmE9ZsXx6","session_id":"8e4c6a49-a8f5-4820-a234-101957ee0803","uuid":"604e0247-e519-4f28-ae5b-97a924f6c029","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:52:51.059Z"}
